text:
Compare the <junit><assertions> code added to 1.6 to https://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/attachment.cgi?id=7141 from bug #21387; it does not support assertions in unforked mode, and looks like it does not even warn you if you try. Options:

1. Make JUnitTask.executeInVM warn:

        if (getCommandline().getAssertions() != null) {
            log("assertions are ignored if running in the same VM.",
                Project.MSG_WARN);
        }

2. Add a method to BaseAssertion to configure a ClassLoader with set*AssertionStatus, and use this in JUnitTask.executeInVM (possibly also in ExecuteJava.execute).
